      "raw_text": "The o. r. & N. announces an espe-\ncially low rate to San Francisco on\naccount of the G. A. r. encampment.\nAugust 1922. .......\n\n\nSuperintendent II. G. Morgan of the\nSpokane Falls & Northern has gone\nto Northport to see how much prog\nress has been made IN remodefing the\ndepot preparatory to establishing at\nthat place the headquarters of the\nline. He will remain there a couple\nof days.\n\n\nChief Engineer J. G. White of the\nSpokane & Occur d'Alene Electric\nrailway is in the city and states that\nvery satisfactory progress is being\nmade in making the roadbed for the\nnew line."
    }
